<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Barclays boss Jes Staley is facing fresh calls to resign after he was dragged into efforts to hunt down the wealth of deceased sex offender Jeffrey Epstein. </p>

<p>Authorities in the US Virgin Islands have ordered JP Morgan, Staley's former employer, to hand over the banker's communications with paedophile Epstein. </p>

<p>Increasing pressure: Barclays boss Jes Staley is facing fresh calls to resign</p>

<p>The renewed scrutiny has prompted activist investor Edward Bramson to renew efforts to remove the banker.</p>

<p>In a letter sent to investors in his fund, Sherborne Investors, Bramson said: 'The kindest thing the board could do for him would be to let him go'. </p>

<p>There is no suggestion of any wrongdoing on Staley's part. </p>
